{
  "stem": "26609.6",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was something like a kindergarten.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they kept her for a few hours afternoon, until, from my work, I came, picked her up there and took her home.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we had to work, because, eh, the Russians took away our homes-- homes, houses, or flats, wherever one lived.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they took-- because they came with their families, with their wives, And they couldn't get anything empty houses there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they took over, took them away from us, left us in the one little room only in the kitchen.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they took-- if one had a three-roomed or four-roomed, eh, flat, or bigger house, they took away everything, and they lived the time there, because it was a lot of them.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They came, eh, not only near, the Russians, from Lwow, like, over the border, but from distant places in Russia, even from, eh, mm, Kurdistan, Dagestan, and all those, eh, places in Russia.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So we had some-- [NON-ENGLISH] us over.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they took away from us everything.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So they left me-- but if one worked, then they left a room over for her, because we worked for them.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That's why it was-- I had to work a half a day, part-time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Otherwise, it were very hard at this time-- very hard.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We had to stay-- to get up very early.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And there were queues for food.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Not much food there, because they needed everything for the-- for their families, the Russians needed.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Eh, so we had to get up early in the morning, with a child in my arms, before going to work, and to stand in a queue.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
